cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.IR. 

The paper proposes a novel method for solving the multiple-instance learning problem, which is a common problem in computer vision applications. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The proposed method involves optimization using stochastic gradient descent, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of a Noisy-OR model and joint optimization of bag and instance labels suggests that it may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves text processing for object discovery, which suggests that it may belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
